OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1773846666
OL,3,CMet to use unprecedented Thames
OL,4,Cstrategy ahead of controversial protest
OL,6,FThe Metropolitan police have said the
OL,7,Fforce plan to use the River Thames to
OL,8,Fblock thousands of protesters from
OL,9,Fclashing in London during the Al Quds
OL,10,FDay march on Sunday 15 March.
OL,12,FOfficials believe this is the first
OL,13,Foccasion that Scotland Yard has relied
OL,14,Fon the river as a physical divide to
OL,15,Fkeep a major protest and its counter-
OL,16,Fdemonstration apart.
OL,18,FThe protest on Sunday will attract
OL,19,Faround 12,000 participants, with
OL,20,Fsenior officers warning even more
OL,21,Fcould attend amid the war in Iran.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G1/10
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
