OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1773846666
OL,3,CMet to use unprecedented Thames
OL,4,Cstrategy ahead of controversial protest
OL,6,FSpeaking to reporters on Thursday, he
OL,7,Fsaid: "While we will protect the right
OL,8,Fto freedom of speech, there is a zero-
OL,9,Ftolerance approach to hate crime and
OL,10,Fanyone who crosses the line can expect
OL,11,Fto face arrest."
OL,13,FThe protest has drawn criticism over
OL,14,Fapparent backing for the Iranian
OL,15,Fregime after its organisers expressed
OL,16,Fsupport for the country's late leader
OL,17,FAyatollah Ali Khamenei.
OL,26,@oD@GOUsD@PO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/10
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1773846666
OL,3,CMet to use unprecedented Thames
OL,4,Cstrategy ahead of controversial protest
OL,6,FThe Government banned the march but
OL,7,Fpeople can still legally assemble and
OL,8,Ftake part in a so-called "static
OL,9,Fprotest".
OL,11,FMr Adelekan said this would be
OL,12,F"immeasurably easier to police".
OL,14,FBut political violence tsar Lord
OL,15,FWalney has warned this could still
OL,16,Fcause serious disorder and blamed a
OL,17,F"loophole" in public order laws
OL,18,Fdepriving ministers of the power to
OL,19,Fstop rallies that stay in one location.
OL,26,@pD@ZOUqD@HO]tD@AOUtD@_O]yD@AOUyD@JO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/10
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
